<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	&#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Journal Title</em> volume no. issue (year): pages.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Study Smarter, Not Harder: Setting Goals to Improve Your Academic Performance</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Journal Title">Student Review</span></em> 
	<span class="hover" title="volume">25</span>, no. 
	<span class="hover" title="issue">5</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="year">2056</span>): 
	<span class="hover" title="pages">10&#45;12</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
